Ontology_Component: The space external to the outermost structure of a cell. Pain may come from extremes of temperature, mechanical damage, electricity or from noxious chemical substances [goid 19233] [evidence IEA]

A neuropeptide is any of several types of molecules found in brain tissue, composed of short chains of amino acids; they include endorphins, enkephalins, vasopressin, and others. They are often localized in axon terminals at synapses and are classified as putative neurotransmitters, although some are also hormones [goid 5184] [pmid 7057924] [evidence TAS]
